textBeforeTable: All events for this episode: ​      A barn was lifted off its foundation and landed on a house southwest of Eitzen while power poles and lines were blown down in Eitzen. Event Narrative A warm front was lifting north across the Upper Midwest and thunderstorms developed along this boundary during the evening of March 16th across southeast Minnesota. Some of these storms produce strong winds which blew down grain bins in Byron (Olmsted County). Power poles were blown down and a barn was lifted off its foundation in and near Eitzen (Houston County).
